body:
## Bevy version

0.16.1 --- also happens on current `main`.

## What you did

Create a white sprite with zero `custom_size`, and add triggers to two sprites to detect pointer pressing.

```rust
use bevy::prelude::*;

fn main() {
    App::new()
        .add_plugins(DefaultPlugins)
        .add_systems(Startup, setup_scene)
        .run();
}

/// For checking press on the small sprite
fn pressed_trigger_interaction_system(
    _trigger: Trigger<Pointer<Pressed>>,
) {
    println!("PRESS SMALL");
}

/// For checking press on the largersprite
fn pressed_trigger_interaction_system2(
    _trigger: Trigger<Pointer<Pressed>>,
) {
    println!("PRESS BIG");
}

pub fn setup_scene(mut commands: Commands) {
    commands.spawn(Camera2d);
    // Here we spawn the zero scale sprite
    commands.spawn((
        Sprite {
            color: Color::WHITE.into(),
            custom_size: Some(Vec2::new(0.0, 0.0)), // <-- !! Important bit
            ..default()
        },
        Pickable::default(),
   )).observe(pressed_trigger_interaction_system);

    // spawn other sprites
    commands.spawn((
        Sprite {
            color: Color::WHITE.into(),
            custom_size: Some(Vec2::new(100.0, 100.0)),
            ..default()
        },
        Transform::from_translation(Vec3::new(200.0, 0.0, 0.0)),
        Pickable::default(),
   )).observe(pressed_trigger_interaction_system2);
}
```

## What went wrong

I would expect that triggers for the sprite with zero `custom_size` wouldn't fire --- it never has any pixels under the mouse. However, this sprite steals all picking interactions --- mouse press no longer registers on the other sprite.

If you change the size of the first sprite to (0.01, 0.01) instead, then things work as expected even without any visible pixels from the tiny sprite.

While uncommon, I ran into this issue while making my sprite size determined by some value that starts at zero, e.g.:

```rust
pub fn sprite_size(sprites: Query<&mut Sprite>, my_val: Res<MyVal>) {
    for mut sprite in sprites {
        sprite.custom_size = Some(Vec2::new(my_val.0, my_val.0));
    }
}
```
This was surprising behaviour that took some debugging to resolve.
